meta {
  name: 1.2 Who is Rolf - NO RAG
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/ask/no-rag
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "Who is Rolf?"
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Beat 1 — the problem (a person it can't know)

  Plain LLM, **no retrieval**. "Rolf" only means something inside *your*
  newsletters; a generic model has no idea which Rolf you mean.

  **Expected:** either a refusal ("Rolf could refer to many people…") or a
  confident guess about some unrelated famous Rolf. Either way, not *your* Rolf.

  Pair with `2.2 Who is Rolf - naive RAG` to show retrieval grounding the answer
  in what the newsletters actually say.
}
